Biker reacts at lightning speed and prevents worse things
On Friday night, a traffic accident occurred on the highway between Machtolsheim and Merklingen, in which a motorcyclist was only slightly injured thanks to his quick reaction.
Car driver overlooked biker
A 44-year-old woman wanted to take her VW from Merklingen to the left on the state road 1230 in the direction of Machtolsheim.
She overlooked the 24-year-old motorcyclist coming from the direction of Nellingen.
Hand and foot brake levers fly away during the collision
The biker tried to evade the car, but he still rubbed it at the rear of the vehicle.
As a result of the stripping, the hand and foot brake levers on the Suzuki were torn down and the driver was no longer able to brake down.
At the moment, he controlled his motorcycle in the green stiffeners next to the road and let it roll out there without falling.
Biker suffers leg injury
Due to the collision with the car, the biker nevertheless suffered an injury to the bei and had to be treated in a clinic.
Mamming: Corona Mass Infection: 174 Harvesters Infected
After a Corona mass infection on a large vegetable farm in Mamming in Lower Bavaria, almost 500 people are quarantined and are no longer allowed to leave the farm.
A security service monitors the ban.
A total of 174 harvesters were tested positive for the Corona pathogen Sars-CoV-2 during the in-line investigation, as reported by the Landratsamt Dingolfing-Landau on Saturday evening.
"Unfortunately, in order to avoid further expansion, we have to take this step to protect the population," said District Administrator Werner Bumeder (CSU).
Previously, seven employees had already been infected in the company - this was the reason for the series test.
The farm is a large vegetable farm that grows strawberries, cucumbers, cabbage and beetroot - but the cucumbers only for insertion glasses.
Mamming is a rural community with a population of about 3,300 not far from Dingolfing with its large BMW plant.
Bumeder appealed to the citizens to keep calm: "According to our information, it is a closed group of people".
On the farm were infected by uninfected employees separated, the site is now surrounded by a barrier fence.
The Greens and the SPD shared responsibility for the state government.
The two opposition factions accused Prime Minister Markus Söder (CSU) and his cabinet of neglecting the control of the housing of seasonal workers.
"This can be a bitter revenge if such local infection events have to be eliminated and regional lockdowns ordered," said Jürgen Mistol, the parliamentary director of the Greens.
The SPD sees this very similarly: "After the Corona eruption in the Wiesenhof slaughterhouse in mid-May, we have already demanded a special control program for farms with crop helpers," said environmental expert Florian von Brunn.
"The hygiene conditions at the workplace and the living conditions in particular need to be strictly controlled from our point of view.
That obviously didn't happen. "
The outbreak came "with announcement".
