Söder expresses himself about the corona situation after mass infecton
Munich - Health Minister Melanie Huml (CSU) has already announced a test offensive for large farms on Sunday.
The press conference will be shown live on our homepage.
The case in Mamming in the district of Dingolfing-Landau has startled authorities and politicians.
Almost 500 crop workers from several countries are currently working on the large vegetable farm, more than a third of them have become infected with the corona pathogen.
The farm is now quarantined and closed with a construction fence.
No one is allowed to leave the site, food is delivered.
The authorities now offer free Corona tests to the more than 3,300 inhabitants of the municipality.
Since the harvest workers had little contact with the local population, the district office so far assumes that the infections have not spread beyond the farm.
"Conscience Bites": Confession of the alleged arsonist of Nantes
"My client was cooperative," lawyer Quentin Chabert told the newspaper.
The defender added, "He deeply regrets the deeds, the confession was for him a liberation."
His mandate was "plagued by bites of conscience and very taken away from the extent of destruction".
In the case of a conviction, according to the prosecutor's office, the man faces ten years imprisonment and a fine of 150,000 euros.
The Gothic St. Peter and Paul Cathedral in Nantes was badly damaged in a fire on Saturday night last week.
The fire broke out in three distant places in the church.
Laboratory tests confirmed the suspicion of arson.
