Because of the coronavirus pandemic, the encounter is held without spectators.
"We are especially looking forward to this game.
It is always nice to come to Frankfurt and meet friends, "explained Kovac.
This is an interesting test in terms of sport, said the 48-year-old.
Before joining FC Bayern Munich, Kovac had coached the Hessen from 2016 to 2018 and led to the victory in the DFB-Pokal.
"A top-class opponent like Monaco is a good test for us with regard to the match against Basel.
Like all the people in Frankfurt, I look forward to meeting Niko Kovac again, "said Eintracht coach Adi Hütter.
The 50-year-old Austrian had succeeded the Croat in the Concord.
In March, the Frankfurt side lost the first round of the eighth round against Basel in their own stadium with a 0 – 3 loss.
