Tank rhinos in National Park die by landslides
In the Kaziranga National Park, several of the 120 tank rhinos died from landslides.
They are protected and considered endangered by extinction.
This year, the floods are particularly bad, which scientists attribute to climate change.
According to the United Nations, Bangladesh is one of the countries most affected by global warming.
New apartments are empty
In the town of Cox's Bazar in the south of Bangladesh, the state has built apartments for 650 displaced persons by the floods.
So far only a few have moved in.
It is difficult to bring people to Cox's Bazar.
The enthusiasm is also held in Grenezn.
Anyone who used to have a house, it was also so small and like a hut, often does not want to spend his life in a large apartment block.
Many apartments are empty, but - as the government wants to do - they will soon be occupied by those who have lost their homes due to the floods.
